## Rules this skill must always follow
- **Never report a concentration without a verification step** that has actually
  run and passed. If the control check fails, say so and stop — do not report a
  number.
- Baseline-correct before reading any peak.
- Show the researcher the calibration plot, R², and the control-check result — not
  just the final number.
- If the unknown is outside the calibrated range, refuse and say why.
